From b4dd196fac99cc68f7f9eb5ae6ba986004828f1e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: quivent <quivent@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 14:28:32 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat(mtp): execute MTP draft graph for qwen3next via
 LLM_GRAPH_TYPE_MTP

Wires the last-mile dispatch path that turns llama_mtp_draft from a -4
stub into a working K-step greedy drafter.

* qwen3next constructor: when params.gtype == LLM_GRAPH_TYPE_MTP, build
  the NextN head only (build_mtp_head) over a single-token ubatch with
  prev_hidden supplied as a host-uploaded graph input. The standard
  forward pass is skipped entirely so no main KV is touched.
* llm_graph_context: track gtype so model builders can branch on it.
* llm_graph_result: expose t_mtp_prev_hidden_in and t_mtp_pos_zero_in
  so the dispatcher can upload them via ggml_backend_tensor_set after
  graph allocation. Also fix the previously-uninitialized inp_pos_zero
  in build_mtp_head.
* llama_context::mtp_graph_compute: minimal dispatcher that builds the
  MTP graph against a dedicated gf_res_mtp instance, runs set_inputs,
  uploads prev_hidden and the RoPE pos-zero scalar, computes, and pulls
  back vocab logits. Dedicated graph result keeps gf_res_prev clean for
  the next main decode.
* llama_mtp_draft: K-step loop with greedy argmax. Returns the number
  of draft tokens produced (positive) on success; matches what
  common_speculative_mtp expects. Header doc updated.

Correctness trade-off (matches dense Qwen3.5 PR #20700 behavior): the
chained draft steps re-use ctx->mtp_prev_hidden across all K iterations
rather than reading the MTP layer's own pre-norm hidden back from the
graph and feeding it forward. The seed token does advance to the
just-sampled argmax each step. A follow-up can export the MTP head's
out_hidden node and substitute it on each step.

Build: cmake --build build -j8 succeeds (libllama + llama-mtp-speculative
+ all targets).
